Betty Compson https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Betty_Compson 0 For the actress who married NYC Mayor Jimmy Walker, see Betty Compton. Betty Compson (born Eleanor Luicime Compson, March 19, 1897 – April 18, 1974) was an American actress and film producer. Most famous in silent films and early talkies, she is best known in her performances in The Docks of New York and The Barker, the latter earning a nomination for the Academy Award for Best Actress. For the_actress who married NYC_Mayor_Jimmy_Walker , see Betty_Compton . Betty_Compson (_born Eleanor_Luicime_Compson , March_19_,_1897 – April_18_,_1974_) was an_American_actress_and_film_producer .
